Flag raised to indicate that the traffic is proxied. It will be raised as soon as possible and on the first server packet in the case of proxies that require a specific classification (asproxy, vtunnel ...). It will be raised in many different cases: we find one of HTTP's standard headers that implies an HTTP proxy (Proxy-Authenticate, Proxy-Authorization), we have a CONNECT method/request, we are above socks4 or socks5, the uri is an absolute one (http://foo.bar), we classified a protocol above HTTP which is tagged as anonymizer. We do not guarantee that all the proxy-detected requests are anonymization/evasion attempts: some applications will make genuine connections over HTTP using proxy stacks to implement data tunnels for example.
